The paper deals with the design and analysis of data structures for metric spaces, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves optimization problems and approximation algorithms, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and algorithms (cs.AL). The use of SDP relaxations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves lower bounds and integrality gaps, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and theoretical computer science (cs.TH).
